Experiment complete. All 8 tests for Conway's Game of Life are passing:

1. ✓ empty input returns empty
2. ✓ single isolated cell dies (underpopulation)
3. ✓ two adjacent cells die (underpopulation)
4. ✓ 2x2 block is preserved (still life)
5. ✓ vertical blinker oscillates to horizontal
6. ✓ overpopulated cell dies
7. ✓ dead cell with 3 neighbors is born (reproduction)
8. ✓ negative coordinates handled

Implementation uses sparse representation (only living cells), supports infinite grid via offset-based neighbor enumeration, and is coordinate-agnostic for negative values.
